  • Method Details

    • identity

      public static <T> ToolChainFactory.ToolChainBuilder<T,​T> identity()
      Creates a toolchain builder that does nothing, but can be used to enforce an input type of a the next link in a chain

      For example a chain of type Chain<T, R> a can feed into any chain of type Chain<? super R, O>. If you were to chain a into an identity of type C such that C super R, now the new chain can only feed into another chain of type Chain<? super C, O>. This reduces the set of possible chains to feed into, and can aid in clarity.

      Type Parameters:
      T - the type to output as
      Returns:
      a new identity chain
